{"type":"message","id":"2bb60c47","parentId":"92a67925","timestamp":"2026-04-14T23:03:14.204Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gim8d2czvdk6_1","toolName":"sessions_list","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"count\": 39,\n  \"sessions\": [\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"origin\": {\n        \"provider\": \"heartbeat\"\n      },\n      \"label\": \"Cron: 5p Progress Report\",\n      \"displayName\": \"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776207784552,\n      \"sessionId\": \"c55fc64c-91a6-4b39-bc25-7d92bc7b2ecc\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 11154,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"running\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1776207783926,\n      \"childSessions\": [\n        \"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:c2d275a5-d70a-4775-a268-fecf4708f133\",\n        \"agent:planner:subagent:63bb70ce-b5f3-48d0-a236-b6cf5d8d7922\",\n        \"agent:planner:subagent:ba49ac6d-ceff-4a9d-b3b1-7b89afdd88cc\"\n      ],\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/c55fc64c-91a6-4b39-bc25-7d92bc7b2ecc.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Now let me compare the current state against the stored baseline:\\n\\n**Baseline (21:37 UTC):**\\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` — running ✅\\n- `cron:e7885813` — running ✅ (new session started 21:34)\\n- `cron:6f3323ef` — done (ended its cycle)\\n- `main` — done\\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258` — running (stale)\\n- Pipeline: HEALTHY\\n- Blockers: none\\n\\n**Current (22:53 UTC):**\\n\\n\\nChecking the session statuses now — the QLHV monitor is still running as expected, the Agent Status session is still active, and the DTLX 5p Monitor has restarted its cycle as normal cron behavior. The main session appears to still be done based on the last heartbeat.\\n\\nLooking at the remaining sessions, the group channels are in expected states, the Telegram direct session has ended as expected, and the cron sessions are running normally. There are some older failed or timeout sessions from earlier in the day that were already cleaned up, so those aren't concerning.\\n\\nComparing against the baseline from 21:37 UTC, the main change I'm noticing is that the `cron:e7885813` Agent Status session started showing as \\\"running\\\" with a timestamp of 22:53, which is a shift from its previous status. Looking at the session timestamps more carefully—the baseline shows `cron:e7885813` was running at 21:37, and it appears to still be running now with an updated timestamp, which suggests the status check at 22:53 is simply reflecting the same active session rather than a new restart. Looking at the session details more carefully, the cron:e7885813 that started at 21:34 is still running over an hour later, which is longer than expected for a typical status report cycle. The main orchestrator session is also showing updates, suggesting these are legitimate long-running processes rather than failures. Looking at the cron sessions more carefully—the Agent Status session is still running after over an hour, which seems unusual for what should be a brief status check, but it's not showing any errors. The other two cron jobs are cycling normally as expected. The group Telegram session ended hours ago and the individual Telegram session also closed, but there's a third session that started even earlier and appears to be the parent of all these cron jobs. I'm also seeing some planner subagents that completed earlier in the day.\\n\\nChecking the session timestamps and statuses against the baseline, everything seems to be operating within expected parameters—the cron cycles are completing as they should, the active sessions match what was running before, and there are no new failures or blockers to flag. The pipeline appears healthy with normal operational noise. I'm noticing the cron:e7885813 session has been running for over an hour, which seems unusual for a status heartbeat that typically completes in under a minute, but there's no failure status recorded, so this appears to be a legitimate extended run rather than a stalled process. Looking at the QLHV group monitor session from earlier, it did manage to send messages through to the group at 21:37, so the Telegram delivery mechanism itself is functioning.\\n\\nComparing the baseline session list against what's currently running, all three cron jobs are still active and cycling normally, and the main Telegram session is still running as expected. The key distinction I'm tracking is that the group monitor itself is the cron that's spawning sub-agents to send reports, not the main orchestrator session, so what I'm seeing here is the parent process that's still active. I'm seeing the telegram:direct session ended at 1776162158012, which is after the baseline at 21:37 UTC, so this is a new change from the previous state where it was still running. Looking at the updated timestamp of 1776207051618, this session is clearly running as of now. The discrepancy is interesting—the session shows as \\\"done\\\" with an end time of 1776162158012 (around 22:02 UTC), but it also has the latest updatedAt timestamp of 1776207051618 (22:50 UTC). This suggests the session ended and then something triggered a refresh or update to its metadata, which would explain why it's appearing as \\\"running\\\" despite the end time. So the Telegram group session ended around 21:49 UTC based on the end timestamp, but the `updatedAt` field shows 22:40 UTC—there's definitely something inconsistent here. Either the session is stuck in a loop of updating itself, or the end time is stale and the session is actually still active. I need to dig into the DTLX group session data to see what's actually going on with the group: agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5168104492\\n\\nThe group session shows status \\\"done\\\" with endedAt 1776149739320, but the DTLX 5p monitor is running again at 22:50 UTC—normal cron behavior since it was marked done at the baseline.\\n\\nNow comparing the baseline state from 21:37 UTC against the current state, the cron:ed2d0b5d is still running and appears stable.\\n\\nThe remaining sessions all check out as expected: cron:e7885813 and cron:6f3323ef are cycling normally, the main session has ended, and the group Telegram sessions are either done or showing the expected lifecycle states. No new failures, no blockers—all three critical cron jobs are running with normal cycle patterns. There are some stale sessions in the list from earlier sub-agents, but they're not part of the current active baseline.\\n\\nI should stay silent on this—no report needed since nothing's actually changed.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Comparing current state vs. baseline (21:37 UTC):\\n\\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` ✅ still running (QLHV 5p — ~4h 16m)\\n- `cron:e7885813` ✅ still running (Agent Status to Lead — ~1h 19m)\\n- `cron:6f3323ef` ✅ restarted to running — normal cron 5-min cycling\\n- `main` ✅ done (expected)\\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258` → `done` (ended ~21:49 UTC — was already stale)\\n- `telegram:direct:6053576134` → `done` (ended ~22:02 UTC — was already stale)\\n- No new failures, no blockers, pipeline HEALTHY\\n\\nAll changes are expected cron cycling and stale session cleanups — nothing new.\\n\\n**Silent. No report.**\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provid