{"type":"message","id":"ed7981c9","parentId":"a56498a3","timestamp":"2026-04-14T23:03:35.891Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The memory_get returned `disabled: true` and `error: \"path required\"`, so memory is not available for reading the heartbeat-state.json file. But looking at the sessions_list data, I can see the current state clearly.\n\nLet me compare against the last known baseline from the main session history messages:\n\n**Last baseline (from session history messages):**\n- cron:ed2d0b5d ✅ running\n- cron:e7885813 ✅ running  \n- cron:6f3323ef ✅ running (cycling normally)\n- main ✅ done\n- telegram:group:-5163901258 → done (ended ~21:49 UTC)\n\n\n- telegram:direct:6053576134 → done (ended ~22:02 UTC)\n- No failures, no blockers, Pipeline: HEALTHY\n\nNow checking the current sessions at 23:02 UTC. The cron:ed2d0b5d session from 21:37 is still running after about 4 hours and 25 minutes, with recent activity just a few seconds ago. The cron:e7885813 session is also showing as running with updates from 15 seconds ago, so that one's still active too.\n\nThe telegram:direct:6053576134 session ended at 22:02 UTC after about 1h 53m, and the cron:e7885813 cycle ended around 22:55 UTC after 1h 31m before restarting. Looking at the main orchestrator session at 22:56 UTC, there were no state changes detected—all the cron cycles, session cleanups, and pipeline health checks were running as expected.\n\nNow I'm checking the current status across all services at 23:02 UTC. The cron:e7885813 session is still running with recent activity from 22 seconds ago, while the telegram:group:-5163901258 session appears to be in a confusing state where it shows as \"done\" with an endedAt timestamp of 21:49 UTC, but the updatedAt timestamp suggests it was actually active more recently. I'm realizing the heartbeat message likely went to the cron:e7885813 session itself rather than the group channel, which would explain why it shows the correct timestamp. Let me cross-reference the other sessions to see if there are any actual state changes I should be tracking. The cron:e7885813 cycle appears to have ended around 22:55 based on the endedAt timestamp, though there's some ambiguity about when it actually restarted. I'm seeing references in the main session messages to a DTLX monitor that ran at 22:55, but I need to figure out if that's the same session or a different one that's cycling. Looking at the session lifecycle, cron:e7885813 ended at 22:55 UTC and restarted about 7 seconds later, which appears to be normal cron behavior. The telegram:direct:6053576134 session ended at 22:02 UTC and was already accounted for in the baseline, so there's nothing new to report here.\n\nNow comparing against the last report from 22:56 UTC, the state at 23:02 UTC shows no meaningful changes: cron:ed2d0b5d is still running at about 4h 25m duration, cron:e7885813 restarted normally at 22:55 UTC, and the rest of the sessions remain in their expected states.\n\nEverything appears stable—no new failures, no blockers, and the pipeline is healthy. The cron cycling and session cleanups are all normal, so there's nothing to flag for this report.","thinkingSignature":"df174093fd277e496d8ef9f540257b027dc736e1b7f8574324a6ce1ba7c30356"},{"type":"text","text":"Silent — no report. All active sessions running as expected. Nothing changed."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":30270,"output":737,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":411,"totalTokens":45362,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776207794215,"responseId":"062dfab34ef0df96c93c8072896d853f"}}
